Nth root

{{task|Classic CS problems and programs}} 
[[Category:Simple]]

;Task:

Implement the algorithm to compute the principal [[wp:Nth root|''n''th root]] <big><math>\sqrt[n]A</math></big> of a positive real number <big>''A''</big>, as explained at the [[wp:Nth root algorithm|Wikipedia page]].



=={{header|JavaScript}}==
Gives the ''n'':nth root of ''num'', with precision ''prec''. (''n'' defaults to 2 [e.g. sqrt], ''prec'' defaults to 12.)

<lang javascript>function nthRoot(num, nArg, precArg) {
  var n = nArg || 2;
  var prec = precArg || 12;
  
  var x = 1; // Initial guess.
  for (var i=0; i<prec; i++) {
    x = 1/n * ((n-1)*x + (num / Math.pow(x, n-1)));
  }
  
  return x;
}</lang>

